1. Fix insect specimen in ethanol, chloroform, and glacial acetic acid (6:3:1) at 4Â°C over night.
2. For 10 minutes each submerge the collar into 40% ethonal (2 times), 70 % ethonal and 100 % (ethonal) (2 times) ethanol at room temperature.
3. methylbenzoate (MB), 50/50 v/v MB and paraffin 60 minutes 
4. paraffin 60 mintues (2x)
5. let dry over night
6. section
